 <span class="floydstyle subheader">Red-lit Balcony</span>
 From the east shines an overpowering roseate light, though the sky is
 still dark, and speckled with stars like freckles of pestilential
 blood.

 A gleaming red form flies towards you through the air.

 That's not the sun.

 When the form comes closer you see that it is an angel dressed all in
 red gauze. A plague angel! Its scarves flutter behind like stage
 flames as it drifts closer.

 The angel hovers several yards past the railing of the balcony. Its
 androgynous smile is hard, carved from rock candy. It reaches into a
 red box tucked beneath its arm, and then casts its hand towards you,
 like it is feeding grain to chickens. Red-black flakes fall on your
 face, sink into your skin. So this is how the plague is spread. You
 always thought it had something to do with bad night air or snakes.

 (At least it's not ghosts.)



